Word Guessing Game
Welcome to the Word Guessing Game! üéâ

Overview
This is a simple command-line word guessing game written in Python. The objective is to guess a randomly selected 5-letter word within a limited number of attempts.

How to Play
Start the Game:

When you run the script, a random 5-letter word will be chosen.
Guess the Word:

You have 7 attempts to guess the correct word.
Each guess should be a 5-letter word composed of alphabetic characters only.
Feedback:

After each guess, you will receive feedback using symbols:
‚úîÔ∏è - Correct letter in the correct position.
‚ùì - Correct letter but in the wrong position.
‚óºÔ∏è - Incorrect letter.
Winning:

If you guess the word correctly, you will receive a congratulatory message based on the number of attempts left.
The game will end immediately upon guessing the correct word.
Losing:

If you exhaust all 7 attempts without guessing the correct word, the game will reveal the correct word and end.
